ney, they would embrace each other. Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Awsat\u0323 lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 97 Grade: Jayyid (very good) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0628\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17061,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/11\/30\/greetings-shake-hands\/","url_meta":{"origin":5764,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Greetings: Best to shake hands, not bow or kiss","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 30, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, when a man among us meets his brother or friend, should he bow for him?\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo.\u201d The man said, \u201cShould he embrace him and kiss him?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cNo.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5761,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/31\/reward-shaking-hands\/","url_meta":{"origin":5764,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Manners: Muslims rewarded for shaking hands","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 31, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Bara' ibn 'Azib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo two Muslims meet each other and shake hands but that Allah forgives them before they part.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2727 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25666,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/21\/prophet-more-mercy-ourselves\/","url_meta":{"origin":5764,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Rahmah: The Prophet more merciful to us than ourselves","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 21, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Umaymah bint Ruqayqah reported: I pledged allegiance to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, with a group of women. The Prophet said to us, \u201cIn so far as you are able and capable.\u201d I said, \u201cAllah and his messenger are more merciful to us than we\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32231,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/16\/fall-like-leaves-shaking-hands\/","url_meta":{"origin":5764,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Greetings: Sins expiated by shaking hands","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 16, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, when the Muslim shakes hands with his brother, both of their sins fall away like the falling of leaves from a tree.\u20